    "# Import necessary libraries\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pypipr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "a668d8e3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

      ]
     },

    },
    {
     "data": {

      "text/plain": [

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Load sample data. We set the max pupil size to 6 mm, to mimic non-baseline corrected data.\n",
    "pm = pypipr.load_simulated_pupil()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(10, 6), sharex=True)\n",
    "pm.plot(ax=ax, label='Original Data', color='gray')\n",
    "pm.plot_light_stimulus(ax=ax, color='yellow', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "ax.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "7d35c007",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x12f221ca850>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate the baseline, and apply the baseline correction. Note. This requires the light stimulus to be set.\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline_duration = 3 # seconds, counting back from light onset\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline_pm = pm.copy()\n",
    "baseline_pm.apply_baseline_correction(baseline_duration)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(10, 4), sharex=True)\n",
    "pm.plot(ax=ax[0], label='Original Data', color='gray', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "baseline_pm.plot(ax=ax[1], label='Baseline Corrected Data', color='blue')\n",
    "pm.plot_light_stimulus(ax=ax[0], color='yellow', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "baseline_pm.plot_light_stimulus(ax=ax[1], color='yellow', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline = pm.calculate_baseline(duration=baseline_duration)\n",
    "ax[0].hlines(\n",
    "    baseline,\n",
    "    ax[0].get_xlim()[0],\n",
    "    ax[0].get_xlim()[1],\n",
    "    color=\"red\",\n",
    "    linestyle=\"--\",\n",
    "    label=f\"Calculated Baseline: {baseline:.2f} mm\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# The new baseline should be at exactly 1.00 (100%)\n",
    "new_baseline = baseline_pm.calculate_baseline(duration=baseline_duration)\n",
    "ax[1].hlines(\n",
    "    new_baseline,\n",
    "    ax[0].get_xlim()[0],\n",
    "    ax[0].get_xlim()[1],\n",
    "    color=\"red\",\n",
    "    linestyle=\"--\",\n",
    "    label=f'New \"Baseline\": {new_baseline:.2f} mm',\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].legend()\n",
    "ax[1].legend()\n"
   ]
  }
 ],
